goals.visualization: scatter plot of group size vs count

goals.question: What is the distribution of unique person values?

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="group", y="count", data=data)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of groups?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(3)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='count', y='person', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    chart.set(xlabel='Count', ylabel='Person')
    plt.title('Who are the top 3 people with the highest count?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    unique_persons = data['person'].nunique()
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='person', bins=unique_persons)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unique person values?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(x=unique_persons, color='red', label=f'Unique Persons: {unique_persons:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
